                            <comment id="12941758" author="dejanb" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 12:46:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in svn revision 795069&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13501218" author="guerrero" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 15:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching unit test that shows messages stop forwarding depending on the order consumer paths are added and removed. See &lt;a href=&quot;http://activemq.2283324.n4.nabble.com/Topic-consumers-are-lost-in-a-cyclic-network-td4659548.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this thread&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13501268" author="gtully" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 16:17:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There seems to be an ordering issue with this fix, as per the new unit test. Lets investigate for 5.8&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13760674" author="gtully" created="Fri, 6 Sep 2013 21:51:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix in &lt;a href=&quot;http://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/activemq/commit/6c5732bc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/activemq/commit/6c5732bc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks for the easymock test case. it helped focus in on the real problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;btw: added the bridge identity to the consumerId generator seed, so that the origin of network consumers is more visible. &lt;/p&gt;
